  "poem": {
    "content": "The airport hummed, a rookie's weary sigh,\nAnother dawn, where shadows drift and lie.\nA little hope, a siege against the grey,\nA setup built for someone to obey.\n\nThe other faces, lost in transit’s need,\nA loyal heart, a silent, planted seed.\nLike cattle driven, onward to the gate,\nA rusty sword, a future sealed by fate.\n\nNo thin excuse can mend this broken flight,\nTo put aside the darkness and the light.\nI need to retire, from battles fought in vain,\nTo direct my soul back to the sun and rain.\n\nThese faded jeans, a comfort and a guise,\nReflecting dreams within my tear-filled eyes.\nWhere loyalty feels like a fading dream,\nLost on Solana's crypto laden stream.",
